<body><div><span><strong>Article Title:</strong> </span><span>The Best Cruise Ports on the East Caribbean</span></div><br />
<div><span><strong>Article Content: </strong></span><br /><span><p>If you are looking to enjoy a relaxing and fun cruise that is filled with thrills and excitement then consider hopping on a ship that takes you around the eastern Caribbean Sea. Eastern Caribbean cruises are popular because many of the ports they stop in have many of the characteristics tourists want when they want to take a trip to the Bahamas.</p>
<div id="allsizes-photo"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5162/5361280448_b48a9d2fbd.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Image Courtesy of <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/pmarkham/5361280448/sizes/m/in/photostream/" target="_blank">Flickr</a></div>
<p>There are dozens of ports along the eastern side of the Caribbean Sea. Some are packed with fun and excitement, while others aren't as great. If you are planning on going on a <a href="http://www.celebritycruises.com/destinations/home.do?dest=CARIB" target="_blank">Caribbean cruise</a>, make sure it includes some of these popular cruise ports on the eastern coast of the Caribbean Sea.</p>
<h3>Philipsburg Port</h3>
<p>Philipsburg is a popular Eastern Caribbean port that is used by many cruise ships. It allows people to have direct access to the islands of St. Maarten/St. Martin. St. Maarten/St. Martin has everything a tourist could want in a Caribbean port. There are tons of shops filled with a variety of souvenirs and items for purchase.</p>
<p>St. Maarten/St. Martin also gives tourists direct access to beautiful beaches. Tourists often love to soak up the sun or take in the beautiful views that are available from some of the many beaches.</p>
<p>Other activities available in the Philipsburg port include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Snorkeling</li>
<li>Yachting </li>
<li>Swimming</li>
<li>Restaurant hopping</li>
</ul>
<h3>San Juan Port</h3>
<p>San Juan is a part of Puerto Rico and is rich in both tourist attractions and historical landmarks. Tourists often spend the entire day exploring the rustic historical city that is filled with fortresses and city ruins.</p>
<p>Other activities in San Juan port include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Kayaking </li>
<li>Hiking through the national forest</li>
<li>Shopping</li>
<li>Swimming </li>
</ul>
<h3>Dominica Port</h3>
<p>The Dominica port is extremely popular because it offers tourists an alternative to the 'traditional' cruise ship ports. Instead of being filled with shops and restaurants, <a href="http://www.dominica.dm/" target="_blank">Dominica</a> is filled with tons of outdoor activities that allow tourists to enjoy the beautiful outdoors. Everything from white water rafting to hiking is available for tourists to engage in while stopping at the Dominica.</p>
<p>One of the most unique features of the Dominica is its geothermal vents. These vents will create a bunch of warm bubbles under the water. Many tourists love to snorkel through them.</p>
<p>Cruises are about relaxing and getting away from reality for a little bit. Consider a <a href="http://abcnews.go.com/Travel/cruise-ship-safety-20-tips-safer-cruising/story?id=15390477" target="_blank">cruise</a> that will take you through one of these great eastern Caribbean ports and you will be able to rest and relax, while being surrounded with many great activities to keep you busy.</p></span></div></body></html>